# Frontend Architecture

The Memor frontend is built using React Native with Expo and uses a modular architecture.

## Technology Stack
- Framework: Expo SDK 52+
- Language: TypeScript
- UI Framework: React Native Paper
- Navigation: Expo Router
- State Management: React Context API, @tanstack/react-query
- Data Storage: Firebase with local-first persistence

## Directory Structure
- [memor/app/](mdc:memor/app) - Expo Router pages and navigation
- [memor/components/](mdc:memor/components) - Reusable UI components
- [memor/features/](mdc:memor/features) - Feature-specific components and logic
- [memor/contexts/](mdc:memor/contexts) - React Context providers
- [memor/hooks/](mdc:memor/hooks) - Custom React hooks
- [memor/services/](mdc:memor/services) - API and service integrations
- [memor/utils/](mdc:memor/utils) - Utility functions
- [memor/constants/](mdc:memor/constants) - Application constants
- [memor/types/](mdc:memor/types) - TypeScript type definitions
- [memor/assets/](mdc:memor/assets) - Static assets and resources

## Key Files
- [memor/package.json](mdc:memor/package.json) - Frontend dependencies
- [memor/app.json](mdc:memor/app.json) - Expo configuration
- [memor/tsconfig.json](mdc:memor/tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
